---
import BrandLayout from '../../layouts/BrandLayout.astro';

const updated = '2026-05-26';
---

<BrandLayout title="Terms of Service — venkata.info" description="Terms that govern your use of Architect Zero.">
  <article class="legal-page">
    <header class="legal-head">
      <div class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of
        <strong>venkata.info</strong> and the <strong>Architect Zero</strong> learning
        platform (collectively, the "Service"), operated by Venkata Sundaragiri ("we",
        "us"). By using the Service, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
      <p>You must be at least 13 years old to use the Service. If you are under the
        age of majority in your jurisdiction, you must have permission from a parent or
        guardian.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Your account</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You are responsible for keeping your account credentials secure.</li>
        <li>You may not impersonate another person, use a false identity, or share
          your account with others.</li>
        <li>You may delete your account at any time; we may suspend or terminate your
          account if you violate these Terms.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Scrape, mirror, or republish lesson content without written permission.</li>
        <li>Reverse engineer or attempt to extract source from the platform beyond
          what is publicly visible.</li>
        <li>Submit spam, malware, or abusive content via any user-generated input
          (comments, display names, newsletter forms, support emails).</li>
        <li>Use the Service to harass, threaten, or harm others.</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to other users' accounts or to the
          underlying infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Content and intellectual property</h2>
      <p>All lesson content, quiz questions, flashcards, videos, code samples, and
        original materials on the Service are © Venkata Sundaragiri, unless otherwise
        attributed. You may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the materials personally to study for the Claude Certified Architect
          exam or related certifications.</li>
        <li>Share short excerpts with attribution and a link back to the source page.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You may not redistribute the lessons or course materials in bulk, sell them,
        or use them to train commercial models without written permission.</p>
      <p>
        References to Anthropic's Claude Certified Architect (CCA) exam are made for
        educational purposes. Anthropic and Claude are trademarks of Anthropic, PBC,
        and this Service is not affiliated with or endorsed by Anthropic.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. User-generated content</h2>
      <p>If you post comments, display names, or other user-generated content, you
        grant us a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to display that content on the
        Service. You retain ownership. You are responsible for what you post. We may
        remove content that violates these Terms or applicable law.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Free service, no warranty</h2>
      <p>The Service is provided free of charge, "as is" and "as available", without
        warranty of any kind, express or implied. We do not guarantee that the
        Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, accurate, or fit for any particular
        purpose.</p>
      <p>Architect Zero is a study aid. It is not a guarantee that you will pass the
        CCA exam or any other certification. Exam outcomes depend on your own
        preparation and Anthropic's evaluation.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, we will not be liable for any
        indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your
        use of the Service. Our aggregate liability for any direct damages is limited
        to USD 100.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Changes to the Service</h2>
      <p>We may add, remove, or modify features of the Service at any time. We will
        make reasonable effort to communicate material changes to active users.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the
        top reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the Service after a
        change constitutes acceptance.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Governing law</h2>
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of New Jersey, USA,
        without regard to its conflict-of-laws principles. Disputes will be resolved
        in the state or federal courts located in New Jersey, USA.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about these Terms, email
        <a href="mailto:sundaragiriv@gmail.com">sundaragiriv@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BrandLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 120px 24px 96px;
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .legal-head { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--brand);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .legal-head h1 {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', Impact, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .legal-updated {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-page section { margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .legal-page h2 {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', Impact, sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .legal-page p { margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .legal-page ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .legal-page li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .legal-page strong { color: var(--white); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal-page a {
    color: var(--brand);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4);
  }
  .legal-page a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--brand); }
</style>
